Rating: 0
I was expecting very little from this recipe, based on the lackluster reviews, but was very pleasantly surprised by the results. First, this recipe is painfully simple, a must for week-nights. Second, I followed several reviewers' advice and added three cloves of garlic to the marinade (which I doubled), and salt-and-peppered the chicken generously before marinating. I figured that any meat merinade that does not include garlic must be a misprint. The chicken marinated for about ninety minutes at room temperature in about two-thirds of the marinade, the rest of which I kept warm on the stove for saucing. I grilled the chicken for sixteen minutes, turning and basting once. The result was a flavorful chicken breast which retained moisture well and received a bright, tangy flavor from the marinade. Served it over Basmati to family from ten to forty five years old, and all liked it very much; which is why I cook in the first place.

