I would give this recipe half a fork, if possible. The marinade was not well balanced at all and imparted a bad taste to the exterior of the chicken. The marinade would be better with less lemon juice and more soy sauce and perhaps substituting chopped garlic for the onion. I marinated the chicken for 4 hours in the refrigerator and an additional 1/2 hour at room temperature before grilling it, but the marinade did not penetrate into the interior of the chicken. The only thing this recipe has going for it is that it was extremely easy to make, but there are many better easy recipes to be found.

