I made this because I wanted something simple and fast, but it was surprisingly delicious. I used it on chicken legs with the skin cut off and meat pierced with a fork to let the marinade penetrate--mine marinated for about 12 hours, and the chicken was juicy and had a lovely lemony flavor. The glaze reduced well, and I served some on the side as a sauce. The only changes I made were to use green onions instead of yellow (personal preference) and to add a tablespoon of chile sauce to the marinade, not to make it spicy so much as to round out the flavors. Overall, one of the best, and yet simplest, marinades for chicken.

