Rating: 0
In reading the previous reviewer, Lisa, I want to remind everyone NOT use the marinade at the table. The recipe says to make the onion mixture (onion, lemon juice, vegetable oil, honey and soy sauce) and use half as a marinade for the chicken. It should be discarded. The recipe states to boil the second half of the onion mixture making it a glaze for the cooked chicken. The second half has not been used with raw chicken; it is not the marinade. Additionally, I wonder why the authors of this recipe thought it was OK to leave the raw chicken out at room temperature for an hour to marinate?

