I made this dish tonight, and as we were eating, we both thought, just so-so. Then my husband said, is there any marinade left to put over the chicken? There was, and this made all the difference. The onions had been soaking up the marinade for a few hours, so they really had a lot of flavor. Maybe I missed something somewhere, but this was not mentioned in the recipe, so I thought I'd share the idea. It really punched up the flavor. I think I will double the marinade next time just so there will be enough marinated onions to pass at the table. Also, I did cut back a little on the lemon and added a little more soy sauce. All in all, I'm looking forward to making it again.

