Rating: 4
This recipe easily moves to four forks with the addition of 1 tablespoon of hot chili sesame oil and increasing the soy sauce to 2 tablespoons. The smell of the chicken on the grill is absolutely riveting... you can just get happy by standing nearby and sniffing... and the promise is carried through in the flavor. The steamed asparagus and rice-orzo pilaf we served with it were perfect. The pilaf is made this way: In a 10" skillet, melt 2 talbespoons of butter over medium heat. Saute 1 cup long-grain rice, 1/3 cup orzo, and 4 oz. sliced tiny mushrooms until grains are brown. Add 2 1/2 cups chicken broth, and cook, covered, over low heat until liquid is absorbed. Stir occasionally. Remove from heat and let steam about 20 minutes. This was a fabulous dinner!

